  "known_issue_BR_B": "The BR-B compute_rk_breit_retarded_algebraic function returns 0 for several convergent Breit-Pauli retarded integrals (e.g. (1s,1s;1s,1s) l=2 gives 0 vs published 83/640 from Bethe-Salpeter \u00a738). The region splitting in _T_kernel_breit_retarded fails when m1<0 AND m2<0 even though the combined integral is convergent. This script bypasses BR-B by using direct sympy integration."
